    &lt;span&gt;Cameroon’s historic malaria vaccine introduction shows signs of success, one year on&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/h1&gt;
            &lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;A year ago, Cameroon kicked off a wave of ground-breaking malaria vaccination campaigns. With nearly 140,000 kids now vaccinated across the country, authorities are already seeing the impact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
